Remove Credit Card sums (Both Square and Normal) from Cash Amounts

Normal Columns

-Cash Sales column

Summary Section

-Total Cash Sales
-Calculated Cash
-Total Cash Payment
-Calculated Cash
-Variance

{color:#4c9aff}Update from call for clarity on above requirements:{color}
{color:#ff991f}Column changes:{color}
Remove “Check Sales” Cash column ensure that the cash column retains existing behavior without credit cards.

{color:#ff991f}Checkbox text:{color}
Update checkbox text to “Credit Card Breakout”

{color:#ff991f}Summary Section Changes{color}
”Remove total check sales”
”Calculated Cash” - remove credit card amounts from calculation
”Actual Cash” - remove credit card amounts from calculation
”Cash from other programs” - remove credit card amounts from calculation
Variance - {color:#ff5630}Subtract{color} “expected Credit Card” Amounts and {color:#36b37e}Add{color} “recorded card” amounts from deposit.
Deposit Amount - Take straight from deposit, and make sure it includes any entered credit card amounts.
Credit card sales - Total credit card sales for Date/Date range across all meal types in report. (always present)

{color:#ff991f}Report Legend{color}

{color:#008da6}The Activity Report provides an operational summary or overview daily activity, with details including meal counts, sales, cash, etc., based on the criteria selected.{color}

{color:#008da6}"Count" and "Meal Sales" do not include 2nd meal.{color}

{color:#008da6}A La Carte = A La Carte items (includes any 2nd meals).{color}
{color:#008da6}Total = Meal Sales +A La Carte (includes any 2nd meals) + Tax.{color}
{color:#008da6}Calculated Cash =  Total Cash Sales + Total Check Sales + Total Cash Payment.{color}

{color:#008da6}Variance = Actual Cash – Calculated Cash + Deposited Credit Cards - Expected Credit Cards{color}

{color:#008da6}Tax is included in the Cash and Debit only.{color}

{color:#008da6}Note:{color}
{color:#008da6}Additional Income is included in the Variance amount.{color}

